Department of Education's Terence Khala speaks to eNCA. Courtesy #DStv403  JOHANNESBURG - Over half of South African children aged four and five are unable to meet expected standards of early learning and physical growth. The Thrive by Five Index evaluated more than 5,000 children in various types of Early Learning Programs.   It is the biggest survey of preschool child development ever attempted in South Africa. The department of education's Terence Khala says the index is instructive as they take on the Early Childhood Development function from the Social Development Department.